OL,6,FAcross the country, 151,630 children
OL,7,Fare homeless in temporary
OL,8,Faccommodation, which Shelter says is
OL,9,Fthe highest number since records began
OL,10,Fin 2004.
OL,12,FThe research from IKEA and Shelter
OL,13,Fshows many families live in cramped,
OL,14,Funsafe, and unhealthy conditions for
OL,15,Fprolonged periods.
OL,17,FIt found nearly half (47%) of homeless
OL,18,Ffamilies were living in these
OL,19,Fconditions for over two years.
