OL,3,CHastings hotspot of children
OL,4,Chomelessness, Shelter charity finds
OL,6,FOne in five households (21%) have
OL,7,Fexperienced safety hazards like faulty
OL,8,Fwiring or fire risks, and more than
OL,9,Fone in three (35%) parents say their
OL,10,Fchildren do not even have their own
OL,11,Fbed to sleep in.
OL,13,FIn addition, more than two-thirds
OL,14,F(68%) of these households struggle
OL,15,Fwith inadequate access to basic
OL,16,Ffacilities such as cooking or laundry,
OL,17,Ffurther compounding the daily
OL,18,Fhardships they face.
